sqlViews.description: Lists entries in the dictionary where the ICD-SMoL code referenced is used both at the main- and sub-catogory level at the same time. This might lead to double counting when doing analysis.
sqlViews.name: CoD: Dictionary entries mixing main- and sub-categories
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
select 
	optsub.name,
	optsub.code
from 
	optionvalue optsub
left join
	optionvalue optmain on 
	split_part(optsub.code, '.', 1) = split_part(optmain.code, '|', 1)

where 
	optsub.optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY') and 
	optsub.code like '%.%|%|%' and
	optmain.optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY') and 
	optmain.code not like '%.%|%|%'
group by
	optsub.name,
	optsub.code
union all
select 
	optmain.name,
	optmain.code
from 
	optionvalue optsub
left join
	optionvalue optmain on 
	split_part(optsub.code, '.', 1) = split_part(optmain.code, '|', 1)

where 
	optsub.optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY') and 
	optsub.code like '%.%|%|%' and
	optmain.optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY') and 
	optmain.code not like '%.%|%|%'
group by
	optmain.name,
	optmain.code;

sqlViews.description: Dictionary entries that do not follow the standard format of ICD-SMoL|ICD10|INDEX
sqlViews.name: CoD: Dictionary entries with invalid code format
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
select 
	name,code 
from 
	optionvalue 
where 
	optionsetid in (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY') and
	code != '[NOT LISTED]' and 
	code not like '%|%|%'
order by sort_order;

sqlViews.description: Dictionary entries where the ICD-SMoL code does not refer to an entry in the ICD-SMoL list.
sqlViews.name: CoD: Dictionary entries with invalid ICD-SMoL reference
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
select 
	name,
	code, 
	split_part(code, '|', 1) as icd_smol
from 
	optionvalue 
where 
	optionsetid in (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY') and
	split_part(code, '|', 1) not in (select code from optionvalue where optionsetid in (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL')) and
	code != '[NOT LISTED]'
order by icd_smol;

sqlViews.description: Terms from the Cause of Death dictionary with ICD codes, for use with IRIS coding software.
sqlViews.name: CoD: Dictionary terms with ICD (for IRIS)

sqlViews.description: Lists the next index number to be used when adding new entries to the dictionary.
sqlViews.name: CoD: Next dictionary index number
sqlViews.sqlQuery:
select 
	left(split_part(code, '|', 3), length(split_part(code, '|', 3)) - 5) as termtype,
	lpad((1+max(right(split_part(code, '|', 3), 5)::int))::text, 5, '0') as nextvalue
from 
	optionvalue 
where 
	optionsetid = (select optionsetid from optionset where code = 'ICD_SMOL_DICTIONARY') and
	code like '5%|%|%' and
        left(split_part(code, '|', 3), length(split_part(code, '|', 3)) - 5) != 'INT'
group by termtype;
